features: Ready Made:Each package includes 2 panels of pinch pleated curtain with 18 hooks(without rings),measuring 40"Wx95"L each panel.

100 Percent Blackout:Sewn with blackout coated lining,room darkening curtains can block out sunlight,uv rays effectively and provide thermal insulation,noise reduction and total privacy protection,which is a perfect choice for baby,night shifter,and people who are sensitive to the light.

Pinch Pleats Design:Each beige curtain panel with 7 pinch pleats generates modern and luxury feel.Linen curtains provide a natural,organic,and textured look that complements a variety of interior styles.By offering linen curtains in various colors,patterns,and lengths,we can cater to customers looking for a casual yet sophisticated window treatment.Hanging these pinch pleat curtains to elevate your windows and increase the aesthetic value to any spaces,bedroom,living room,nursery,office,etc.

Multiple Hanging Ways:The luxury curtain has 3 hanging options to meet your different home décor needs:back tabs(4 inch),clip rings or ring hooks.Please note that 18 hooks are in the package but clips and rings are not included.Two weighted hems sewn at bottem increase the draping effect.
Easy Care:Curtains are machine washable in cold.Gentle cycle and do not bleach.Tumble dry low and iron on lowest setting as needed. Customized sizes are available upon request.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very good but not perfect; attractively priced. Long delay in shipping.
reviews.reviewText: The linen-like fabric is attractive. It's very sheer but that is irrelevant because the liner is thick. It completely darkens the room -- except where sewn. Little dots of light show through. It would be a challenge to buy the fabric for the cost of the finished product (about $60 for a pair of 63 inch curtains when I bought them), so I consider them a very good value. They are not perfect. I purchased five pair and a few had slightly uneven hems and/or the blackout curtain liner didn't line up with the linen front perfectly. I had to hem them, so this was more of an annoyance to me than it would be to the typical customer.I bought a few initially as a try-out so that if I didn't like them, I would have less to return. The first shipment came quickly; the second sat at the "ordered, not shipped" status for about a week. Perhaps those sets came directly from China. Check delivery date: prime didn't mean two day delivery from the time of order. (But yes, once they showed as 'shipped' then it was two days and they did come on the date predicted.)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Just what I was looking for for kitchen eating room. Didn't care if they were black out cause they don't have that rubbery feeling liner. Very nice linen look. Don't need ironing. Just let them hang a few days. As another reviewer stated. Put some clips on back of pleats and they'll hang straight. I took them off after a few days. These definitely look like much higher end curtains. Just buy them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The quality is exceptional!
reviews.reviewText: I don’t usually write reviews. The quality is excellent on these drapes. They are packaged neatly to avoid extra wrinkles. A quick steam had them looking great. I ordered the wider width and they look like custom drapes. Also block out the sun . The linen look fabric is very nice. They are a nice white / natural color. I highly recommend them if you like the elegant look of pinch pleated drapes. They hang perfectly also!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful Curtains at a GREAT price!
reviews.reviewText: I shopped all over for curtains for a client's great room. They needed black out since so much sun comes in and warms up the room. We needed a lot of curtains to cover 2 whole walls of windows, and we also needed to stay within budget! I wanted something pleated that looked high end without paying for a designer label, and these curtains are it! Worth every penny! Looks exactly like something from Pottery Barn but a fraction of the price. The quality is top notch! The pleats are well made, and I love that they are weighted at the bottom! I did have to steam A LOT of wrinkles out when I first hung them up, but that's to be expected. In the end, they were exactly what I envisioned for the room. If you're debating, get them! You will not find a better value for the price! I will definitely be recommending these to future clients, and I may even find a window or two in my own home that need them. Overall, these were a great buy!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect! Amazingly perfect!
reviews.reviewText: These curtains look exactly like the picture - hang beautifully, pleats are perfect spaced and they block out the light. Arrived in nicely packaged and the few wrinkles seem to be dropping out without needing steaming - a real plus. You will not regret this purchase - I bought four pairs and each was - OK - perect!
Fit well, great insulation and light blocking. Colour exactly as shown, hooks provided. Love them. Highly recommend.
Great quality and true black out. Worth every penny!

I bought the pink drapes. They hang nicely. However, I am disappointed with the lining. I have been searching for a white lining.
